{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require a 2/3 majority in the HoC to scrap/withdraw from human rights provisions",
        "additional_details": "I am concerned that some political movements are calling to abolish vital rights legislation to benefit large corporations. I believe it is important in safeguarding civil society that we make no compromises in protecting human rights for future generations.\r\n \r\nI believe disregard and contempt for human rights have resulted in barbarous acts which have outraged the conscience of humankind. No matter our politics, I feel it is our duty to uphold human rights for all and protect our children from political corruption.",
        "background": "We call for a two thirds majority of all sitting MPs to be required to abolish or withdraw from:  the Equality Act 2010, GDPR laws, the Data Protection Act 2018, the European Convention on Human Rights, the European Court of Human Rights, the 1951 Refugee Convention, and the CRPD.",
